The art at first looked great, then as it progressed it started looking incredible. But then the art quality begins to tank at page 447 almost as if it was done by a different artist. The beginning you had a general idea where the story was going, but then the pacing began to drag a bit and the author decided to make us take in two stories at the same time which was a bit unnecessary. The mom was thrown into the story only to be completely cut out of it, and to avoid having to make the story any longer was lazily killed off… even though I didn’t want the mom to end up with the dad/uncle I felt that could’ve been resolved better. Also some drama between the two female protagonists would’ve been nice, because idk, one of them is banging the other one’s dad??? Instead the pink haired girl’s reaction to her friend being in a relationship with her father was dumbed down to a simple “Ew.” However the first 400 pgs I enjoyed, just the rest went down the drain and the ending was… not the best.
